				\begin{document}$$^{222}\hbox {Rn}$$\end{document} from detector surfaces causes the dominant background in current liquid xenon time projection chambers (TPCs) searching for dark matter. A significant reduction is required for the next generation of detectors which are aiming to reach the neutrino floor, such as DARWIN. 222Rn\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
